    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bce575d2_8fddacd0",
        "filename": "snapshot/win/system_snapshot_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 213,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-16T17:34:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "buffer (or, renamed, vendor_identifier) may not be NUL-terminated at all. Consider the notes about NUL-termination in the RegQueryValueEx() documentation.\n\nYou should consider vendor_identifier_size. You should call base::UTF16ToUTF8() with a size, explicitly. Note that in the general case, a REG_SZ may or may not be NUL-terminated already, you’ll need to detect and handle appropriately.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 213,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "dde6a0dba04424e28cf24e4b3429865fd6784856",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3b033767_8796ee5a",
        "filename": "snapshot/win/system_snapshot_win.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 213,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-16T17:34:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To avoid having the indentation start to get out of hand, prefer early returns:\n\n  HKEY key;\n  if (RegOpenKeyEx(…) !\u003d ERROR_SUCCESS) {\n    return std::string();\n  }\n  crashpad::ScopedRegistryKey scoped_key(key);\n\n  DWORD type;\n  // …\n  if (RegQueryValueEx(…) !\u003d ERROR_SUCCESS || type !\u003d REG_SZ) {\n    return std::string();\n  }\n\n  return base::UTF16ToUTF8(buffer);",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 213,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 213,
        "endChar": 6
      },
      "revId": "dde6a0dba04424e28cf24e4b3429865fd6784856",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
